<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="294" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1154,1971]" box="[151,511,1154,1179]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
Length. ♂ 
<quantity box="[263,367,1154,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.68" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" unit="mm" value="3.68">3.68 mm</quantity>
, ♀ unknown
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1154,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1190,1215]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Description.</emphasis>
Relatively robust, general color light brown with darker markings; head, pronotum, and scutellum with brown stripes and discal maculations (
<figureCitation box="[779,909,1226,1251]" captionStart="FIGURE 8 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1960,1982]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,230,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,220,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 8 – 10. Habitus of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 8. Head, pronotum, scutellus, and left wing in dorsal view; 9. Face; 10. Habitus and coloration." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Figs. 8, 10</figureCitation>
). Crown with black spot above each ocellus, slightly longer medially than next to eye (
<figureCitation box="[628,742,1262,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 8 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1960,1982]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,230,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,220,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 8 – 10. Habitus of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 8. Head, pronotum, scutellus, and left wing in dorsal view; 9. Face; 10. Habitus and coloration." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 9–10</figureCitation>
). Face brown, flattened, with two parallel lines running from apex of vertex across frontal suture to antennal pits. Ocelli orange. Frontoclypeus, medially flattened, surface brown with many transverse brownish bands on each lateral suture. Genae, clypellus, and lorum with pale brown with form typical of genus (
<figureCitation box="[471,541,1370,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 8 – 10" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1960,1982]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,230,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,220,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 8 – 10. Habitus of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 8. Head, pronotum, scutellus, and left wing in dorsal view; 9. Face; 10. Habitus and coloration." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with hind margin dark brown. Legs and ventral sclerites of thorax dark brown. Abdomen entirely black except genital capsule. Genital sclerites brown with black setae. Forewing macropterous with brown veins. Hind wing translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1154,1971]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
Male genitalia. Apical lobe of pygofer moderately long, broad, with simple setae. Anal hook long directed caudoventrally (
<figureCitation box="[340,415,1514,1539]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Valve anterior margin excavated medially, articulated with pygofer and fused with subgenital plates. Subgenital plates extended to apex of pygofer, slightly tapered, fused on midline in basal half, apices truncate, posterolateral angles rounded, (
<figureCitation box="[699,771,1586,1611]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Style thin, long (
<quantity box="[990,1099,1587,1611]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.30 mm</quantity>
), bearing long setae on outer edge, twisted at base, marginal teeth poorly developed, apex produced on outer angle and toothed on inner angle (
<figureCitation box="[159,276,1658,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Figs. 1, 5</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long (
<quantity box="[493,586,1659,1683]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
) V–shaped in lateral view, nearly straight beyond atrium, shaft strongly dorsoventrally flattened (
<figureCitation box="[436,546,1694,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Figs. 3–5</figureCitation>
), apex with pair of short, preapical retrorse spines (
<figureCitation box="[1136,1207,1694,1719]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Connective broad, shieldlike, with anterior margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[617,687,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
