<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1371,1756]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1587,1612]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hamilton, 1998" authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1998" box="[630,900,1587,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ceratagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ana">
<emphasis box="[630,709,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. ana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton" box="[720,900,1587,1612]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (1998) The species of the North American leafhoppers Ceratagallia Kirkaldy and Aceratagallia Kirkaldy (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 130, 427 - 490. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 130427 - 4" type="journal article" year="1998">Hamilton, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Baker, 1896)" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[962,1287,1587,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigeloviae">
<emphasis box="[962,1116,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. bigeloviae</emphasis>
(Baker, 1896)
</taxonomicName>
, but may be distinguished by the following combination of features: (I) apex of aedeagus linear (curved in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1998" box="[1213,1288,1624,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ceratagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ana">
<emphasis box="[1213,1288,1624,1647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. ana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1313,1423,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Figs. 3–4</figureCitation>
); (II) style slender, bearing large setae, base large (
<figureCitation box="[701,766,1659,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); and (III) connective short (long in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1179,1328,1660,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bigeloviae">
<emphasis box="[1179,1328,1660,1684]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. bigeloviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1422,1659,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[160,1421,231,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,223,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. Male genitalia of Ceratagallia brailovskyi sp. nov. 1. Left style, dorsal view; 2. Connective; 3. Aedeagus, lateral view; 4. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 5. Male genitalia complex; 6. Plates, ventral view; 7. Pygofer, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1045707/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oman" authorityYear="1933" box="[151,387,1695,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ceratagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordida">
<emphasis box="[151,387,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">Ceratagallia sordida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1998" box="[403,479,1696,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ceratagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ana">
<emphasis box="[403,479,1696,1719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. ana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pinedo-Escatel &amp; Dietrich, 2017" authorityName="Pinedo-Escatel &amp; Dietrich" authorityYear="2017" box="[537,696,1695,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ceratagallia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brailovskyi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[537,696,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">C. brailovskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[705,796,1695,1720]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[705,796,1695,1720]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
share similar male genital characteristics (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (1998) The species of the North American leafhoppers Ceratagallia Kirkaldy and Aceratagallia Kirkaldy (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 130, 427 - 490. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 130427 - 4" type="journal article" year="1998">Hamilton 1998</bibRefCitation>
) and probably represent a plesiomorphic lineage (see discussion by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton" box="[972,1146,1731,1756]" pageId="4" pageNumber="297" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (1998) The species of the North American leafhoppers Ceratagallia Kirkaldy and Aceratagallia Kirkaldy (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 130, 427 - 490. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 130427 - 4" type="journal article" year="1998">Hamilton 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
